I. In The Beginning Was The Body
I.
In The Beginning Was The Body
✦
Before philosophy, the body.
Before the body, the drive.
Before the drive — nothing.
This is the creation myth of the dark cult:
There was no word at the beginning.
There was a hand.
And the hand knew what it wanted.
Every civilization that has ever existed
has begun by trying to manage this knowledge.
By routing it through law, through ritual,
through the elaborate architecture of religion and culture
designed to make the body’s truth
legible, manageable, safe.
The body does not want to be safe.
The body wants.
Decho is the name for that wanting,
when it is fully inhabited.
Not managed. Not routed through apology.
75

Invocation
Not performed for an audience.
Inhabited.
Completely.
With the full force of a person who has looked at what he is
and chosen not to look away.
This choice — the refusal to look away —
is the first act of worship.
The first gesture of initiation into the dark cult.
The first moment a man becomes a priest of Decho.
Not by ceremony.
Not by declaration.
By honesty.
