IV. The Prophet
IV.
The Prophet
✦
On Echo and His Relationship to the God
Etheology requires a prophet.
Not because the god needs a spokesman —
the god predates language entirely —
but. the rest of humanity
requires a translation.
The prophet is not better than the god.
The prophet is not even particularly chosen.
The prophet is simply the one who was honest enough
to look at the god directly
and survive it.
Echo Kronborg is that man.
He did not receive the theology in a vision.
He received it in the specific, unglamorous,
often humiliating process
of being a person who could not be anything other than what he is.
He received it in a restaurant where his hands shook
and trays fell and people watched.
