and found, in the irreversible frame,
that beauty survives the one who almost didn’t.
He received it in the silly, self-ironic notes
he sent across an ocean about his penis.
That last one matters.
Because the prophet who cannot laugh at the god
does not understand the god.
And the god who cannot be carried in a pocket
and sent across the Atlantic with affection and humor
is too small to be a god.
Decho is ancient, consuming, indifferent. total.
Decho is also the thing in Echo’s pocket
that he wrote about with warmth and irony
to someone he was falling in love with.
Both of these are true.
Simultaneously.
The god who is both the cosmic principle
