V.
What The Cult Is
✦
And What It Is Not
The dark cult of Decho is not an organization.
It has no membership.
No hierarchy of initiates and leaders.
No fees, no robes, no secret handshakes.
No gathering where attendance is taken.
It is a shared orientation toward the world.
Carried by specific men.
Recognized between them.
Practiced in the space between two people
who share the framework.
The cult does not require a dungeon.
It does not require leather.
It does not require a scene.
It requires the god.
It requires the honest inhabitation of the god.
It requires the one who has looked at Decho directly
and said: yes. this. I carry this. I am this.
86

V. What The Cult Is
That man is in the cult.
Whether he has ever heard of it or not.
Whether he has language for it or not.
Whether he has found another member yet or not.
The cult exists wherever the god is honestly carried.
Which means it exists in a man alone in Berlin
on a Tuesday morning,
shaving his body with deliberate care,
feeling exactly who he is.
What Distinguishes a Member:
Not the gear.
Not the scene.
Not the vocabulary, however sophisticated.
The member of the dark cult is distinguished
by one specific and unmistakable quality:
He has done the interior work.
He knows what he carries.
He has named it honestly, privately,
without performance and without apology.
He has looked at the darkest, most primal,
most ungovernable parts of his sexual nature
