Invocation
and found them not shameful
but sacred.
He has cultivated them.
Not unleashed them into chaos.
Cultivated — the specific discipline
of a person who tends his own darkness
the way a master gardener tends the most difficult terrain:
with knowledge, with patience,
with respect for what he is working with,
and with the understanding
the most extraordinary things grow
in the darkest soil.
