VI. The Three Stations
VI.
The Three Stations
✦
On the Hierarchy Within the Cult
The dark cult of Decho has three stations.
They are not a ladder.
They are three different relationships to the god —
three different ways of carrying him,
three different ways of being carried by him.
The First Station: The Initiate
The initiate is the one who has recognized the god
but not yet found a Master to enter through.
They carry the submissive nature.
They know what they are.
They have been honest with themselves about the self they want to
feel —
the specific aspirational sexuality
the dark framework makes possible.
They are sovereign.
Not incomplete.
Not waiting to be completed by dominance.
89

Invocation
They are fully themselves — and that self
is oriented toward surrender
to the right force.
The initiate is the most demanding station.
Because surrender — genuine surrender,
not collapse, not compliance, not performance —
requires more self-knowledge than dominance.
You must know precisely what you are
before you can give it completely.
The Second Station: The Priest
The Priest is the Master.
The conductor through whom the god moves most visibly.
He is not the god himself.
This distinction matters.
The Priest who mistakes himself for the god
becomes a tyrant.
He begins to believe his authority is absolute,
self-generated, requiring no accountability.
He becomes dangerous —
not in the sacred sense that Decho is dangerous,
but in the ordinary human sense
90

VI. The Three Stations
of a man with unchecked power
who has confused the channel with the source.
The true Priest knows he is a conductor.
He is responsible for what moves through him.
He is responsible to the one he holds.
He is responsible to the god
which means he is responsible to the truth —
about his own nature,
about his own failures,
about the specific dark night
that almost broke him
and the even more specific rebuilding
that proved his authority was real.
The Priest who has survived his dark night
and returned to service
is the most powerful figure in the cult.
Not because he is now untouchable.
Because he is now proven.
The Third Station: The Order
Between Priests — between Masters who share the framework —
a third station that is less a rank
than a space between equals.
