The temperature does not compete — it compounds.
Two fields recognizing each other.
Two currents in the same conductor.
What passes between them is not rivalry.
It is recognition.
The specific, rare, almost unbearable relief
of being in the presence of someone
who requires no explanation.
The Order in the dark cult is not friendship.
Though it may include friendship.
It is the specific gravity that forms
between people who share a sacred orientation.
The silent acknowledgment.
The lifting that happens without announcement.
