XI. The Rite Of Initiation
XI.
The Rite Of Initiation
✦
On How One Enters
The dark cult does not initiate through ceremony.
It initiates through recognition.
The initiation happens in a specific and irreproducible moment —
the moment. two people who carry the complementary natures
are in each other’s presence
and both of them understand,
without a word being necessary,
what they are to each other.
This moment cannot be manufactured.
It cannot be scheduled.
It cannot be performed into existence.
It arrives.
And when it arrives —
when the framework is genuinely shared,
when the god is present in the room,
when the Priest sees the Initiate and the Initiate sees the Priest
and both of them feel the temperature change —
the initiation is already complete.
105

Invocation
Everything that follows is the ceremony.
The initiation itself was the recognition.
The Three Tests of Genuine Initiation
Not every recognition is genuine.
The community is full of people who speak the language
without inhabiting it.
The dark cult requires three tests:
The first test: does the framework survive the ordinary?
The scene is easy. The Tuesday morning is the test.
If the dynamic exists only in the scene —
if it requires choreography to survive —
the framework is not shared.
It is borrowed for an occasion.
The second test: does the body report truthfully?
The body does not lie.
When the framework is present, the body knows.
When it is absent, the body knows that too.
The disappearing erection.
The specific flatness of desire
that no performance can recover.
Trust the body.
The third test: does the god survive the dark night?
The framework that cannot survive difficulty
106

XI. The Rite Of Initiation
is a framework in fair weather only.
The genuine initiation produces a dynamic
that holds. the floor gives way —
not because either party is performing endurance
but for the god is real enough
to survive the darkness that tests him.
Three tests.
The framework survives the ordinary.
The body reports truthfully.
The god survives the dark night.
These are the marks of genuine initiation.
Restraint
Berlin is a city where intensity appears easily.
One evening I had a long and beautiful encounter with a woman whose presence carried both confidence and fragility. We walked through the city for hours
before deciding she would stay the night.
But I follow a rule carefully. Thefirst nights are for conversation, for closeness,
for understanding the outline of another mind. Not for the sudden theater of
power.
So we slept beside each other and nothing happened.
The next morning, as I prepared to leave, she asked if we could have sex before
I went. I declined gently. She asked again.
This time she clung to my leg while I was standing in the hallway putting on
my boots.
"Hurt me," she said suddenly. "Kick me."
107

Invocation
For a moment I stood still. Not because I was tempted, but. the situation
revealed something important. Power had appeared in the room, but it had appeared in the wrong form. Not recognition. Not alignment. Volatility.
And volatility is not devotion.
I pulled my leg free and left.
Some thresholds must not be crossed. Knowing which ones — that is the
discipline the practice requires.
Later I understood something that eMaster must eventually learn: dominance is not the freedom to take whatever is offered. It is the discipline to refuse
what should not be taken.
The Master must refuse power more often than he takes it.
108

XII. The Rite Of The Marked Body
XII.
The Rite Of The Marked Body
✦
On Inscription as Sacred Act
The dark cult’s most intimate rite
is the marking of the body.
Not tattooing. Not scarification.
Though these belong to the same theology.
The marking that is specific to this rite
is the marking that leaves evidence.
The Priest who marks what he claims
is performing the most ancient sacred act:
inscription.
The word is from the Latin inscribere —
to write into.
Not onto. Into.
The writing that becomes part of the surface
rather than sitting on top of it.
To mark the body of the one you own
is to write your presence into them.
To make the evidence of the god
visible on the surface of the offering.
109

Invocation
This is why the Priest who marks and then abandons
has committed a theological error.
The inscription requires the inscriber to remain.
You do not write your name in a book
and then burn the library.
Marking carries responsibility.
The evidence of the god on the body
is also the evidence of the Priest’s covenant.
I was here.
I remain.
110

XIII. The Rite Of the Circle
XIII.
The Rite Of the Circle
✦
On How Priests Relate to Each Other
When two Priests of Decho meet —
when two people who carry the god genuinely
are in the same space —
a specific protocol.
Not spoken. Not performed. Felt.
The protocol is this:
Recognition first.
Acknowledgment of what the other is carrying.
The specific gravity between two forces
that do not need to compete
because neither of them is diminished
by the other’s existence.
Then: lifting.
What does lifting mean between Priests?
It means the conversations that can only happen
between those who share the framework.
The specific honesty that becomes possible
when pretense is unnecessary.
111

Invocation
The question asked directly:
how do you carry the god today?
Is the weight manageable?
Have you found the one who completes the circuit?
It means the specific generosity
of sharing what you have learned.
Not as advice. Not as correction.
As offering — one Priest to another.
Here is what my dark night taught me.
Here is where the god went quiet in me
and how I found him again.
It means the laughter.
Because Priests of Decho who cannot laugh
have confused severity for depth.
The god is serious.
He is also — in the right company —
hilarious.
The absurdity of being a person who carries an ancient god
in a body that also needs groceries and sleep.
The comedy of the primal and the domestic.
The silly self-ironic note about the penis
sent across the ocean to someone you are falling in love with.
The god survives the laughter.
