On Sustaining The Flame
✦
How the Charge Is Maintained
The most common failure in the dark cult
is not betrayal. Not collapse. Not dark nights.
It is drift.
The slow, almost imperceptible drift
of a charge that was real
becoming a habit that is comfortable.
The dynamic that was once alive
becoming the dynamic that is simply present.
Furniture. Wallpaper.
The hierarchy that exists in name
but has stopped being felt.
This is not a failure of love.
It is a failure of attention.
The charge is sustained by feeding.
Not intensity.
Attention.
114

XIV. On Sustaining The Flame
What Feeds the Charge
The shared reading of the world.
Two people in a café.
A man walks in.
The glance between the Priest and the Initiate
that acknowledges what both of them see.
No words. A frequency.
