That the framework is still alive between them.
Small rituals, precisely kept.
Not the grand protocols.
The small ones.
The hand at the back of the neck
in an unremarkable location.
The text that arrives mid-afternoon
containing nothing but: I see what I see.
And he knows exactly what it means.
The morning that begins with
a specific, brief, unremarkable gesture
that says: I remember what we are.
The honest conversation.
