Before the practice, the god.
I am not in the dungeon.
I am in the Tuesday.
I am in the supermarket.
I am in the canal light.
I am in the shaved body
moving through a city
that does not know my name
and feels my field anyway.
I do not require ceremony.
I require honesty.
The ceremony is for your benefit.
