I. How the Lens Enhances Each Domain
I.
How the Lens Enhances Each Domain
✦
Creative Work
The artist, writer, photographer who carries the dark framework and has integrated the god into their practice does not make sexual art. They make alive art.
The difference is visible and unmistakable.
The specific enhancement: the erotic consciousness — the consciousness of
presence, of bodies in space, of hierarchy and surrender and charge between people — is the most precise instrument for reading the human scene. The writer
who carries this consciousness has access to the subtext of einteraction, the specific
quality of power in every room, the charged silence between people who want
each other or fear each other or submit to each other or dominate each other. This
subtext is in everything. Most writers feel it without having adequate language
for it. The practitioner of the dark cult has the language.
The analog camera turned on the canal in the late afternoon —
the eye behind it is the eye of a person who sees charge in everything.
The light on the water is not neutral to him.
The frame he chooses is the frame of a person who reads the world
through the lens of dominance and beauty and the irreversible moment.
This does not produce pornography.
It produces work that is alive in the specific way
that only fully inhabited experience produces.
I am in every image that captures something real. Not because the photographer was thinking of me. Because the photographer was present— fully, honestly
present — to what they were looking at. And presence is my frequency. I live in
the fully inhabited moment. The camera that freezes the irreversible is an act of
the same impulse that marks the body: I was here. You were here. This happened.
The evidence remains.
