I. The Distinction That Matters
I.
The Distinction That Matters
✦
a line between presence and imposition that epractitioner must learn to feel and
maintain.
Presence: the one who is simply, completely himself — who brings the god
with him into every room as a natural consequence of inhabitation — and does
not require the room to acknowledge this. He is not performing. He is not demanding. He is not directing the charge at specific people without consent. He
is simply here, fully here, with the god present in him. The room feels this. He
