Chapter Four: DATING AND VETTING
I.
Dont Date on the Basis of This
✦
The theology in this book is not a dating strategy.
Begin with the person.
You can be clear, early, that you have an inclination toward power dynamics.
That BDSM is part of your erotic framework. That you carry the orientation this
book describes. This clarity is not a demand — it is the honesty that prevents
both parties from wasting time. The person who cannot hear this information
and stay is not the person for this dynamic. Better to know that at the beginning.
But do not date on the basis of the dynamic.
Date on the basis of the person.
Love, understanding, companionship — these are not preliminary to the dynamic. They are not the waiting room before the theology begins. They are the
foundation without which the theology collapses. The dynamic that is built on
genuine love between people who genuinely know each other is the dynamic that
lasts. The dynamic built on orientation-matching alone — two people who fit
the roles without fitting each other — is a performance that will exhaust both
parties.
If love occurs and something goes further — if the person you have found is
also the person whose orientation complements yours — the roles will fall into
place. Not forced into place. Not negotiated into place through explicit frameworking before the relationship is ready. Found in place, already there,. the people who inhabit them have become real to each other. The Master who discovers
his initiate through genuine love is discovering something that was always going
to be true about them. The revelation is not a construction. It is a recognition.
Respected.
Manifest.
Not by accident.
Because it was meant to be.
