Chapter Five: THE ORDER IN PRACTICE
I.
The Code of the Order
✦
Brotherhood in the dark cult operates through a specific and unspoken code. Not
written rules — the code is felt, recognized, practiced between people who share
the orientation.
Recognition Without Performance
The genuine Priest does not perform for other Priests. The need to establish
dominance, to demonstrate the god’s presence, to prove the authority — this is
the behavior of a person who is not certain of what he carries. The genuine Priest
has no need to perform for someone who carries the same god. The god in him is
recognized by the god in the other. Performance would be redundant. Worse —
it would be an insult to both.
The code: arrive as you are.
The god will be recognized
or he will not.
Either way, no performance is required.
Lifting, Not Competing
The misunderstanding of the community — that dominant men compete —
has already been addressed theologically. Here it is addressed practically.
What lifting looks like between Priests:
The honest question: how are you carrying the god today? Is the weight manageable?
The specific generosity of sharing what you have learned — not as advice, not
as correction, but as offering. Here is what my dark night cost me. Here is what I
found on the other side. Take what is useful.
252

I. The Code of the Order
The conversation that is only possible inside the shared framework: I had the
dark night. I lost the architecture. I rebuilt from the wreckage. The god is still
here. Is yours? Yes. Good. We continue.
The Laughter
The brotherhood that cannot laugh is not a brotherhood.
It is a performance of brotherhood.
The god is real. The god is ancient and consuming and indifferent and total.
The god is also — between two people who carry him honestly, who have done
the interior work, who have no need to perform solemnity for each other — the
source of the specific comedy of the sacred in the ordinary.
The absurdity of being a person who carries an ancient phallic deity in a body
that also requires sleep and groceries and occasionally sends silly notes across the
Atlantic. The comedy of the primal force navigating the U-Bahn. The specific
hilarity of two people who carry gods discussing this over coffee in a city that has
no idea.
The laughter is not the diminishment of the god.
It is the god at full inhabitation.
Comfortable enough in his carrier to be funny.
Real enough to survive the joke.
253

Chapter Five: THE ORDER IN PRACTICE
II.
How to Find the Order
✦
The brotherhood does not advertise itself. It does not have a location, a meeting
time, a flag.
It is found through the specific recognition the previous chapter described.
The field that is felt before the introduction. The quality of presence that reads
as inhabited rather than performed. The specific ease of one who knows what
they carry and has stopped apologizing for it.
The practitioner finds the Order by being findable.
By carrying the god honestly.
By inhabiting the body deliberately.
By being present in the world as what he is,
without performance and without concealment.
The finding takes care of itself.
