III. The Order and the Initiate
III.
The Order and the Initiate
✦
The Circle is between Priests. The question arises: what is the relationship between the Order and the initiates — the people who carry the submissive orientation, who belong to the dynamic as the other half of the circuit?
The answer is precise: the Order and the dynamic are different communities
that may overlap but are not the same.
Initiates are not members of the Order in the same way Priests are. They
are honored within it through the dynamic — through the specific relationship
with the Priest whose circuit they complete. The Order honors the initiate not
as a member of the Priests’ community but as the specific person who makes the
Priest’s priesthood complete. Without the genuine initiate, the Priest carries the
god alone. The Order understands this.
Between Priests who share the framework,
the initiates are honored as what they are:
the most essential people in the cult.
The ones without whom the Priest is only a carrier,
never a Priest.
Because the god requires an object for his claiming.
Requires the one who yields.
Requires the full circuit.
The Priest alone is half a god.
The Priest with the right initiate
is the god, complete.
