A Note on the Author
A Note on the Author
✦
On the Construct Called Echo
Echo Kronborg is the author of The Dark Hierarchy. This is the only book
published under this name.
Echo Kronborg is a literary construct — a fictional author given a name and a
city and a god,. the material he carries can exist in the world at the appropriate
distance from the person who wrote it. The copyright page names that person.
The cover names this one. The gap between them is intentional and structurally
necessary, in the tradition of Samuel R. Delany’s use of the fictional frame in his
most explicit work: the fiction of the author creates the space in which the truth
of the text can be spoken.
What is true of Echo Kronborg: he was born in Sweden and lives in Berlin.
He works in instant analog photography, in poetry, in the making of irreversible
frames. He carries a god whose name is one letter longer than his own.
He has questioned the foundation. Sat in a kitchen at two in the morning wondering whether the god is loneliness with better syntax. Counted lines.
Watched the architecture fail under conditions it was not built to survive. Shook
in a restaurant. Walked carefully through an interior where the floor had recently
given way.
He rebuilt anyway.
Not from certainty.
From honesty.
That is the only foundation that holds.
The language is Echo’s.
The frequency is not.
The structure was never invented.
It was recognized.
The words end here.
275

